---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — PlayShip"
  description="Terms governing the use of PlayShip, a Google Play submission and rejection-recovery service operated from the United Kingdom."
>
  <main class="container legal">
    <p class="eyebrow mono">TERMS OF SERVICE</p>
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="updated mono">Last updated: 24 May 2026</p>

    <p>
      These Terms govern your use of the PlayShip website and any submission
      service you purchase. By engaging the service or paying an invoice you
      agree to these Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      PlayShip is operated as PlayShip UK (sole trader, Avinash Sreekumar),
      based in Camberley, United Kingdom. References to "we", "us", or "PlayShip"
      mean the sole trader.
    </p>

    <h2>2. The service</h2>
    <p>
      PlayShip helps independent developers submit Android apps to the Google
      Play Store, complete required compliance fields (Data Safety, content
      rating, store listing), and recover from policy rejections. Service tiers
      and inclusions are described on the pricing section of the homepage.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
    <p>
      Service is available to individuals and registered businesses worldwide
      who legally own or are authorised to publish the Android app being
      submitted. You must be 18 or older.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Your responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide a working AAB or source build, accurate metadata, and timely Play Console release-manager access.</li>
      <li>Hold all rights, licences, and consents required for the app and its content.</li>
      <li>Comply with the Google Play Developer Programme Policies. PlayShip configures and submits; final policy compliance is your responsibility as the publisher of record.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Turnaround</h2>
    <p>
      Stated turnaround times begin once we have received the AAB, signing key
      details, Play Console access, and complete intake answers. Delays caused
      by missing inputs extend the timeline.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Pricing &amp; payment</h2>
    <p>
      Prices shown on the site are in GBP or USD as listed. Payment is made in
      advance via Stripe, Wise, or PayPal. Receipts are issued by email.
    </p>
    <p>
      Prices shown are inclusive of any UK VAT where applicable. PlayShip UK is
      currently below the UK VAT registration threshold (£90,000 turnover);
      should this change, prices will be updated to indicate VAT separately.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Refunds &amp; cancellation</h2>
    <p>
      Refund and cancellation rules are set out in the
      <a href="/refund">Refund &amp; Cancellation Policy</a> and form part of
      these Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      You retain ownership of your app and all assets you provide. Deliverables
      we create for you (store listing copy, screenshots) become yours on full
      payment. We may reference the engagement in a portfolio listing unless you
      ask otherwise in writing.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      We do not guarantee Google Play approval, ranking, downloads, or revenue.
      Google may reject or remove apps at its sole discretion. To the maximum
      extent permitted by law, our aggregate liability for any claim arising out
      of the service is limited to the amount you paid for that engagement.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. The courts of
      England and Wales have exclusive jurisdiction over any dispute arising
      out of or in connection with these Terms or the service.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms:
      <a href="mailto:avinashsreekumar007@gmail.com">avinashsreekumar007@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 760px;
    padding-block: 80px;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--approved);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  h1 {
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  h2 {
    margin-top: 40px;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .updated {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 12px;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  p, li {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  li {
    margin-block: 6px;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--line-strong);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--ink);
  }
</style>
